        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "Ann Koehler",
          "email": "amk@cray.com",
          "date": "2014-07-14 17:29:24.000000000",
          "tz": -300
        },
        "subject": "LU-5341 ptlrpc: rpc times out in unregistering phase",
        "message": "LU-5341 ptlrpc: rpc times out in unregistering phase\n\nIf the reply to an rpc is received before Lustre is notified\nthat the request has been sent, the task making the request may sleep\nuntil the rpc times out. Both the rq_reply_unlink and rq_req_unlink\nflags must be cleared before an rpc can be completed. When the reply\nis received, rq_reply_unlink is reset and the  waiter on the rpc wait\nqueue is woken up. If rq_req_unlink has not been reset at that time,\nthe rpc is unregistered and the waiter goes back to sleep. When\nLustre is then notified that the request has been sent,\nrequest_out_callback resets rq_req_unlink but it only wakes up the\nwaiter if the event type is an UNLINK. If the event type\nis a SEND, the waiter waits until the timeout on the the wait queue\ntriggers.\n\nThis mod also does a bit of code cleanup: removes an unnecessary\ncheck for a condition that has already been tested in an LASSERT;\nadds the request and reply unlink flags to DEBUG_REQ messages.\n\nSigned-off-by: Ann Koehler <amk@cray.com>\nChange-Id: I1cbf465d11750c1495a3e8bf2267c392e9c08414\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
